-- module `reexport2` — re-exports `helper` from `reexport`, which itself
-- re-exports `defs.helper` (a TWO-HOP re-export chain: defs -> reexport ->
-- reexport2). Added for PR #912 review: cross_file.jsonl's `rHelper` query
-- only exercises ONE hop (defs -> reexport); this file plus via2.mdk proves
-- the whole-project topo-sort orders a chain of MORE than one hop correctly
-- (reexport2 must be indexed after reexport, which must be indexed after
-- defs — a naive "single dependency" ordering could get this wrong even
-- when the one-hop case passes).
export import reexport.{helper}
